    <item>
      <title>The Weekly Challenge - 367</title>
      <link>https://theweeklychallenge.org/blog/perl-weekly-challenge-367/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 30 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://theweeklychallenge.org/blog/perl-weekly-challenge-367/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;table-of-contents&#34;&gt;TABLE OF CONTENTS&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;hr&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;1-headlines&#34;&gt;  1. &lt;a href=&#34;#HEADLINES&#34;&gt;HEADLINES&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;2-sponsor&#34;&gt;  2. &lt;a href=&#34;#SPONSOR&#34;&gt;SPONSOR&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;3-recap&#34;&gt;  3. &lt;a href=&#34;#RECAP&#34;&gt;RECAP&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;4-perl-review&#34;&gt;  4. &lt;a href=&#34;#PERLREVIEW&#34;&gt;PERL REVIEW&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;5-raku-review&#34;&gt;  5. &lt;a href=&#34;#RAKUREVIEW&#34;&gt;RAKU REVIEW&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;6-chart&#34;&gt;  6. &lt;a href=&#34;#CHART&#34;&gt;CHART&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;7-new-members&#34;&gt;  7. &lt;a href=&#34;#NEWMEMBERS&#34;&gt;NEW MEMBERS&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;8-guests&#34;&gt;  8. &lt;a href=&#34;#GUESTS&#34;&gt;GUESTS&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;9-task-1-max-odd-binary&#34;&gt;  9. &lt;a href=&#34;#TASK1&#34;&gt;TASK #1: Max Odd Binary&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;10-task-2-conflict-events&#34;&gt;10. &lt;a href=&#34;#TASK2&#34;&gt;TASK #2: Conflict Events&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;HEADLINES&#34;&gt;HEADLINES&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;hr&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Welcome to the &lt;code&gt;Week #367&lt;/code&gt; of &lt;code&gt;The Weekly Challenge&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;We completed &lt;code&gt;7 years&lt;/code&gt; of the weekly challenge last week on &lt;code&gt;25th March&lt;/code&gt;. I published a &lt;a href=&#34;https://theweeklychallenge.org/blog/seven-years-of-pwc&#34;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;blog post&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt; to celebrate the occassion.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Thank you &lt;code&gt;Abigail&lt;/code&gt; for your &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/manwar/perlweeklychallenge-club/tree/master/challenge-366/abigail&#34;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;contributions&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Thank you to all team member for helping with testing the app. Please continue for few more days. If you accepted the invitation and not installed the app yet, then please do so now. I need your help. If anyone wants to help me, please send me your email linked to Google Play Store account. I will then send you the invitation. I have had many suggestions, some already implemented and some would be done soon.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>7 Years of The Weekly Challenge</title>
      <link>https://theweeklychallenge.org/blog/seven-years-of-pwc/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 25 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://theweeklychallenge.org/blog/seven-years-of-pwc/</guid>
      <description>&lt;br&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;7-years-of-the-weekly-challenge&#34;&gt;7 Years of The Weekly Challenge&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Today marks seven years since we began &lt;code&gt;The Weekly Challenge&lt;/code&gt; mission. It all started with just a handful of us tackling challenges in &lt;code&gt;Perl&lt;/code&gt;. Soon after, &lt;code&gt;Raku&lt;/code&gt; joined the gang, and we began to grow steadily thanks to the incredible support from both the &lt;code&gt;Perl&lt;/code&gt; and &lt;code&gt;Raku&lt;/code&gt; communities.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;A few months into the journey, someone shared a solution in &lt;code&gt;Python&lt;/code&gt; for the first time. That was a lightbulb moment for me; I decided right then to open the challenge to all programming languages. Today, we host solutions in over &lt;code&gt;100&lt;/code&gt; different languages. While &lt;code&gt;Perl&lt;/code&gt; and &lt;code&gt;Raku&lt;/code&gt; remain our foundation, &lt;code&gt;Python&lt;/code&gt; has climbed the ranks to become the most popular guest language.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
